==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Solvability
<hw>Solv`a*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>solvabilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or
state of being solvable; <as>as, the <ex>solvability</ex> of a
difficulty; the <ex>solvability</ex> of a problem</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The condition of being solvent; ability to pay all
just debts; solvency; <as>as, the <ex>solvability</ex> of a
merchant</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solvable</ent>⟦br⟧
